lead_paragraph: Satguru Sivaya Subramuniya swami, a native Californian who sought spiritual meaning in India as a young man and became the spiritual leader of Sri Lankan Hindus, died on Tuesday at his ashram on the Hawaiian island of Kauai. He was 74. Satguru Sivaya Subramuniya swami (soo-bra-MOON-ya SWA-mee) helped build more than a dozen Hindu temples around the world, including what he called the first Hindu church in the United States.
abstract: Satguru Subramuniyaswami, native Californian who became Hindu spiritual leader, dies at age 74; photo (M)
